         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Kew Sept 20/62 ¶ My dear Mueller ¶  ¶ I have this day received with many thanks the cheque for £30.0.0. The beautiful little grass from Darling ¶  enclosed we cannot name at all. You had sent it befor...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.09.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Kew Sept 20/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have this day received with many thanks the cheque for £30.0.0. The beautiful little grass from Darling<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Darling river, NSW?</p>
               </note> enclosed we cannot name at all. You had sent it before from the Barrier range.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW.</p>
               </note> — I have sent it to Col. Munro at Bermuda, &amp; will let you know his answer. When it comes.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Hooker to M, 24 December 1862.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I must leave it to Bentham to write to you about the Australian Flora &amp; your collections &amp;c. I am quite unable to enter upon the subject being literally overwhelmed this year with work &amp; visitors of all kinds so that my Botanical affairs are getting into sad arrears.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <name key="Welwitschia">Welwitschia</name> has taken me many weeks study &amp; will cost me many more to finish it. It will take 13 plates of the Linneean Transactions to do its scanty justice; for it is incomparably the most marvellous plant ever found in any country.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1863).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am delighted to hear that your health keeps good &amp; that you are still so successfully &amp; usefully employed, though I do hope you will take care of your health &amp; take warning in time. My Father has been troubled all summer with his skin complaint, which affects his ancles &amp; hence his walking — he is much better now, &amp; goes to the country in a day or two.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham is in the country, I do not know when he returns to Kew.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Harvey &amp; his wife<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Harvey married Elizabeth Lecky Phelps on 2 April 1861.</p>
               </note> spent some weeks here, we like the latter extremely, she is very lively agreeable sensible &amp; a charming companion to him in every way suited.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Welwitschia">Welwitschia</name>
            </p>
         </div>
